About the Opportunity:

The Senior Financial Planning & Analysis Manager is responsible for overseeing the company's management accounting function, including reviewing financial performance and providing actionable insights to drive business decisions.¬†

This position includes managing capital reporting to the APRA, ensuring compliance with regulatory standards and timely submissions. Requiring a strong blend of financial analysis, regulatory knowledge, and technical proficiency in ERP systems.¬†

Responsibilities include:

Support strategic decision-making by providing financial modelling and business case analysis for new initiatives and investments and act as a trusted advisor to senior management, delivering insights that support strategic and operational decisions.¬†
Oversee the development of annual budgets, quarterly forecasts, and long-term financial projections.¬†
Identify risks and opportunities within the budget and forecast, providing actionable recommendations.¬†
Perform in-depth analysis of financial results, comparing actuals vs. budget, and identifying key drivers of performance.¬†
Develop and distribute management reports, dashboards, and KPIs to highlight financial trends, risks, and opportunities.¬†
Identify and implement process improvements to streamline forecasting, reporting, and analysis activities.¬†
Continuously review and enhance Financial Planning & Analysis practices, ensuring they align with industry best practices and company goals.¬†
Monitor Regulatory Capital Requirements and assess the company?s capital position against APRA's minimum capital requirements, ensuring alignment with regulatory standards.¬†
Review and ensure all capital-related reports meet APRA's reporting standards, deadlines, and requirements.¬†
Contribute to the development of capital plans, including projections of capital adequacy and capital actions.¬†
Contribute to mergers, acquisitions, and other strategic projects by providing financial insights and analysis.¬†
Develop and provide opportunities for employees to engage in professional development activities.¬†

About You:

As our preferred candidate, you will have:

A bachelor?s degree in Finance, Accounting, Economics and hold an MBA, CFA, or CPA.¬†
At least 10 years+ years of experience in financial planning and analysis¬†
Ability to lead, motivate, and develop a team¬†
Ability to clearly articulate complex financial information and insights¬†
General insurance experience preferred however not mandatory.¬†
Strong proficiency in financial modelling using Excel, SAP, Hyperion, Oracle, Anaplan.¬†
Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills, with a keen attention to detail.¬†
Strong communication and presentation skills, with the ability to convey complex information to stakeholders.¬†
Ability to interpret complex financial data, identify trends, and extract actionable insights¬†
Expertise in applying accounting standards and regulations (such as IFRS) to ensure accurate financial reporting¬†

Experience required

Proven success leading SRE, IT operations, or support teams in enterprise data or AI platform environments.
Deep understanding of modern SRE practices including incident management, automation, monitoring, capacity planning, and disaster recovery.
Experience managing multi-disciplinary teams including operations, incident response, and engineering support.

Bachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs Degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Technology, or related field.

What‚Äôs in it for you?

Employment Type: Full time¬†

#LI-MM1

Most job ads for data engineers talk about ‚Äúexciting opportunities‚Äù and ‚Äúfast-paced environments.‚Äù Translation: you‚Äôll be cleaning up spaghetti pipelines for the next two years.

This role isn‚Äôt that.

You‚Äôll be the one setting the direction. The one deciding how data gets used, stored, and scaled. The one whose work powers AI models, analytics, and commercial decisions, not just another person duct-taping together broken queries.

Here‚Äôs what you‚Äôll actually be doing:

Building pipelines in Azure that don‚Äôt collapse under their own weight.
Designing data architecture that can scale without burning money.
Creating infrastructure that makes machine learning models work in the real world.
Partnering with product and commercial teams so data isn‚Äôt just ‚Äúavailable‚Äù but useful.
Putting proper governance and observability in place
What you need to bring:

Strong Azure knowledge: Data Factory, Synapse, Event Hubs, Functions, Storage.
Databricks, Elasticsearch, Python or .Net
A handle on data modelling, governance, and security that goes beyond theory.
Communication skills that don‚Äôt make commercial people back slowly out of the room.
Extra brownie points if you‚Äôve:

Worked with Snowflake, Airflow, Kafka, MLflow, Feature Stores.
Built AI or propensity models that actually got used.
Seen the inside of a SaaS or startup and lived to tell the tale.
What‚Äôs in it for you:

Flexible hours and remote work ‚Äì no surprises there.
The chance to build a data strategy from scratch, not inherit one from 2012.
A culture where you won‚Äôt be punished for learning.
Work that directly influences the success of the product
This isn‚Äôt a role for someone who wants to be told what to build. It‚Äôs for someone who wants to shape the whole data landscape.

Job Title: Director, Commercial Payments Practice Lead, Visa Consulting & Analytics
Ad Text:
